@Node LanciareEP "To Run EasyPrint"

  From Workbench
  ==============

    EasyPrint can  be  started  from  the  Workbench  like  any  other
  program: just doubleclick on its icon.
  
    You can set a "PRIORITY" tool-type using the Workbench information
  menu choice and a "UNIT" tool-type for  specify  the  unit  of  your
  printer (usually 0).
  
  Example:

    PRIORITY=-1

  From Shell
  ==========

    EasyPrint can be started from the Shell. Template:

    FILE:           The name of the image to load
    
    PRIORITY/N:     The priority of EasyPrint's task

    UNIT/N:         The unit of your printer

  Example

    1.> EasyPrint FILE image.iff PRIORITY=-1
@EndNode

@Node Informazioni "What is Easy Print"

 What is Easy Print
 ==================

    Easy Print is a utility written to enhance the printing of pictures
  (coloured or black & white) on the Amiga.

    What distinguishes Easy Print from  the  numerous  other  printing
  programs existing on the market, besides the exceptional quality  of
  the  results,  is the capacity to exploit the abilities of the Amiga
  itself, even with the cheaper @{"CONFIGURATIONS" link Configurazione}
@EndNode

@Node Configurazione "What Configuration does it Need?"

 What Configuration does it Need?
 ================================

    Easy Print was created on  an  Amiga  1200  for  Amiga  1200,  but
  naturally it works on every superior configuration.

    Really Easy Print needs only two things:

   - A Graphic Printer (the selected one in the System Preferences)
 
   - The Operating System 3.0 or above

   - A 68020 (or higher) processor

    For example, on an unexpanded Amiga 1200 it is possible  to  print
  coloured pictures (with a 24 bit per pixel precision) on a  full  A4
  page with the maximum density.

@EndNode

