@Node ACheServe "Why Register?"

 Why  Register?
 ==============

    Registering to Easy Print  activates  some  options  actually  not
  working (disabled):

    - Saving of the elaborated image in IFF24 format

    - Loading of images in the JPEG (16 million of colours) format

    - Loading of images through datatypes (GIF, X-BitMap, TIFF, Targa,
      QRT, PCX are enclosed in the archive)

    - Work screen with 256 colours for better rendering of the  24 bit
      format of the image kept in memory

    - Possibility of @{"CROPPING" link Taglia} a section of the image, of  elaborating
      and  printing  it separately from the whole picture (useful, for 
      example, to eliminate borders, for text, or to print only a detail
      of the image)

    - Possibility of bending of a free number of degrees the dither of
      printing  for each  of  the fundamental @{"COLOURS" link Colori} (cyan, magenta,
      yellow and black) for minimizing the tendency of the  human  eye
      to  notice  the  horizontal  and vertical lines generated by the
      standard dithers.

    - Possibility of dephase the dithers of printing for each  primary
      colour to optimize blending of colours.

    - POSTER option, for printing Posters of every size!

    - Activate inks compensation to correct ink impurities 

    - Use of Virtual Memory on disk (also on Amiga without MMU, as the
      Amiga  1200),  for  loading  images  of every size without being
      limited by the amount of RAM


    To each registered user a package will be sent  through  the  mail
    containing:

    - The latest version of Easy Print written by  me  (with  all  the
      above mentioned functions enabled).

    - A lot of printing-dithers  (actually  11)  to  be  used  with
      EasyPrint. 
@EndNode

@Node Registrarsi "How can you Register?"

 How can you Register?
 ====================

    To register, it is enough to send me a Postal Money Order for  $25
  (USD) and @{"TO CONTACT ME" link Contattarmi} (by phone, mail or electronic mail) and  to
  give me your data.
@EndNode

@Node Installare "How to Install EasyPrint"

 How to Install EasyPrint:
 =========================

    To install Easy Print is very simple. You have only  to  click  on
  the 'Install' icon to start the automatic  sequence  or  to  do  the
  following actions:

    - To copy the file 'reqtools.library' to your LIBS: directory

    - To be sure that the "Dithers" and the "Loaders" drawers and  the
      "EasyPrint.info"  icon  file  are  in   the  same  directory  as 
      EasyPrint.

  Warning:

    Before using EasyPrint it is important to be sure that the  correct  
    printer is properly selected in the System Prefernces.
@EndNode

@Node UsareEP "How to Use Easy Print"

 How to Use Easy Print
 =====================

    Running Easy Print will bring into view:

    - the working screen, in which two rulers indicate the size of the
      page and that of the image relative to it;

    - the main window,  which  allows  access  to  all  the  different
      functions of the program.

    The work screen, besides representing the page  to  print,  allows
  selection of the component of the image to be showed  on  it  (cyan,
  magenta, yellow or black) through a gadget placed at the crossing of
  the two rulers.

    The main window consists of the following three parts and gadgets:

      Part 1: Project
      ===============

    @{" Preferences "  link Preferenze}  @{"   Iconify   "  link Iconifica}
    @{" Information "  link Main_Informazioni}  @{"     Exit    "  link Esci}

      Part 2: Image
      ==============

    @{"  Load  "  link Carica}  filename  @{"  Save  "  link Salva}

         dim_x      @{"  Aspect X   " link Aspetto}
         dim_y      @{"  Aspect Y   " link Aspetto}
    
    @{"   Balance   "  link Bilancia}  @{"    Crop     "  link Taglia}
    @{"   Modules   "  link Moduli}  @{"    Show     "  link Mostra}

      Part 3: Print
      ==============

    @{"    Size     "  link Modifica}   @{"   Density   "  link Densita}
    @{"   Colour    "  link ColoreCMG}   @{"   Dither    "  link Retino}

    @{"             PRINT            " link Stampa}
@EndNode

@Node   Preferenze  "Preferences"

 "Preferences" Window:
 =====================

    This window consists of the following gadgets:

  Display:
  ========

    Allows selection of the screen-mode of screen used by Easy Print.

  
  Aspect:
  =======

    Using the two numeric gadgets you can modify the aspect  ratio  of
  the pixels of the screen used by  Easy  Print  to  better  suit  the
  monitor.  Instead,  the  gadget "Aspect" will calculate these values
  according to some predefined data.

  
  Size:
  =====

    It sets the size of the work screen of Easy Print.

  
  Palette:
  ========

    It changes the colours of the screen of Easy Print.

  
  Ruler:
  ======

    The first (cycle) gadget allows the choice of  which  of  the  two
  rulers (horizontal or vertical) has  to  be  set  according  to  the
  quantity (expressed in centimetres) inserted in the second (numeric)
  gadget.

  
  Unit of Measure:
  ================

    Yuu can select if the unit  of  measure  must  be  centimetres  or 
  inchs. This selection will change:

   - The lenght of rulers
   - The dimensions indicated in the main window


  Easy Print De Luxe:
  ===================

    @{"OPTION NOT ENABLED!" link Registrarsi}

    It allows access to the 256 colour mode of  Easy  Print,  useful
  for better rendering the 24 bit per pixel of the picture.


  Printing with Smoothing:
  ========================

    For printing a picture, even if large few square  centimetres,  it
  needs to be enlarged by a factor of at least 1:10. That  causes  the
  enlarging  of  the pixel of the image and so it can happen to obtain
  printing in which the "small square" of the pixel are  well  visible
  to  the  naked eye. Smoothing avoids that unpleasant effect by means
  of shading of the colours of two adjacent pixels.

  
  Lines per strip:
  ================

    It sets how many lines the program will print  in  a  passage.  It
  must be noted that these lines are  not  picture-lines (that  is  in
  pixels),  but printer-lines (equal to  the printer's  Y  density per
  inch). Obviously the more the lines the more the memory used by  the
  program.

    NOTE: The number of lines per strip does not have any influence on
    ~~~~  the quality of the print.

  
  Save Balancing:
  ===============

    It snapshots the balancing  settings  for  maintaining  them  when
  loading a new image.


  Rendering:
  ==========

    In the printing phase a screen will  be  opened  (behind  all  the
  others  existing)  in  this  mode;  here  EasyPrint  will  show  the
  rendering of the image to be printed.

    NOTE: The mode  has  no influence  on  the  quality  of  printing.
    ~~~~~

  Virtual Memory:
  ===============

    @{"OPTION NOT ENABLED!" link Registrarsi}

    It allows use of the hard disk to memorize the data of  the  image
  instead of using RAM.

    It is possible to choose to use it or not by selecting one of  the
  following possibilities:

    NEVER use:
    ~~~~~~~~~
        EasyPrint will never use virtual memory.

    Use  when  NEEDED:  
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    
        EasyPrint will try to memorize the picture's data in  RAM;  if
      there is not enough memory it will automatically use the virtual
      memory on disk.

    ALWAYS use:
    ~~~~~~~~~~
      
        EasyPrint will use ONLY the virtual memory for memorizing  the
      data, even if the amount of RAM were enough for doing that. This
      option can be useful on Amigas with only few MB of RAM


 Directory:
 ==========

    @{"OPTION NOT ENABLED!" link Registrarsi}

    It selects the directory in which to save the data of the image to
  print.


 Save:
 =====

    The previously listed parameters will be saved on disk.


  Use:
  ====

    Use the previously listed parameters (these settings will be  kept
  until the next computer reset).


  Cancel:
  =======

    It leaves the settings unchanged.
@EndNode

@Node Iconifica "Iconify"

  Iconify:
  ========

    Easy Print will be reduced to an icon  on  the  Workbench  screen.
  This do not cause the loss of the picture in memory.

    When the icon of an IFF file (or, in the  registered  version,  of
  any other format for which a datatype is present) is dropped on  the
  EasyPrint  icon,  the  relative image will immediately be loaded and
  the work screen will be re-opened.

@EndNode

@Node Main_Informazioni "Information"

  Information:
  ============

    Some information about the program, the author, and the rightful
  @{"THANKS" link Ringraziamenti}..

@EndNode

@Node Esci "Exit"

  Exit:
  =====

    It will end Easy Print...

  The settings concerning: 

    - Dimensions of the page
    - Dimensions of the picture on the page sheet
    - Color Separation
    - Ink Compensation
    - Density of printing
    - Dither used

  will be memorized in a file called  "EasyPrint.def"  placed  in  the
  same  directory as EasyPrint, to be utilized  in  the next session
  of work.
@EndNode

@Node Carica "Load"

 Load:
 =====

    An IFF image of any type (normal Amiga, IFF24,  EHB,  HAM6,  HAM7,
  HAM8, JPEG and DATAYPES (in the registered version)) will be  loaded 
  into  memory.
@EndNode

@Node Salva "Save"

 Save:
 =====

    @{"OPTION NOT ENABLED!" link Registrarsi}

    The data in memory will be saved in  IFF24 format, applying the  set
  @{"BALANCE" link Bilancia}.

@EndNode

@Node Aspetto "Aspect X Y"

 Aspect X Y:
 ===========

    It allows viewing and/or modification of the aspect of  the  image 
  pixels.  If  nothing is inserted  the  value will be restored to the 
  original ones  of the image.
@EndNode

@Node Bilancia "Balance"

 Balance Window:
 ===============

    The Window "Balance" allows modification of the colouring  of  the
  picture by operating on 5 different aspects.

  
  Balancing:
  ==========

    It allows increase or decrease of the fundamental component of the
  colour (red, green and blue or, see the option "Mode", cyan, magenta
  and yellow).

    Mode (RGB/CMY):
    ===============

      The @{"COLOURS" link Colori} are modified respectively using the  Red-Green-Blue
    modality  (additive  synthesis)  or  the  Cyan-Magenta-Yellow  one
    (subctractive synthesis).

  
  Gamma:
  ======

    It varies the gamma of tint of each colour. Positive  values  will
  clarify the intermediate tints keeping unaffected both the black and 
  the white. Negative values will darken the intermediate tints (again, 
  black and white are not altered).

  
  Contrast:
  =========

    Raising this parameter will cause the  image  to undergo  a  major
  separation between bright colours (which will  be  more  brightened)
  and  dark  colours (more darkened);  decreasing  the  parameter will
  cause the image's colours to be levelled on mean values.

  
  Brightness:
  ===========

    It is used to  brighten  (positive  values)  or  darken  (negative
  values) the image.


  Saturation:
  ===========

    It is useful to make colours more "live" (positive values) or more
  "gray" (negative values).


  Use:
  ====

    It will apply the values of balancing to the picture, but allowing
   them to be re-modified after reopening the window.


  Test:
  =====

    It will temporarily apply the values of  balancing  to  the  image
  showing the result on the work screen.


  Apply:
  ======

    It will definitively apply the values of balancing to the image.


  Cancel:
  =======

    It will cancel any settings, keeping the active precedent (at  the
  opening of the window) ones.
@EndNode

@Node Taglia "Crop"

 Crop Window:
 ============

    @{"OPTION NOT ENABLED!" link Registrarsi}

    It can be used to select (also with the mouse) limited portions of
 images for being printed. Note that  the part not selected will still
 be kept in memory.

  
  Top & Left:
  ===========

    They set the left upper limit of the box.

  
  Base & Height:
  ==============

    They set the dimensions (expressed in pixels) of the base  and  of
  the height of the portion of image to be cropped.


  Apply:   It will execute definitively the cropping of the image.
  ======


  Use:     It will execute the cropping, keeping in memory the  entire 
  ====     image.


  Cancel:  It will leave the image unmodified.
  =======
@EndNode

@Node Mostra "Show"

 Show:
 =====

    It will display the loaded picture (showing the  effect  of  the
  @{"BALANCING" link Bilancia}) in HAM8 mode (HAM6 on non-AGA machines) for the coloured
  images  and  in 64 tones of gray (16 on non-AGA machines) for the
  black and white ones.

    By pressing the right mouse button it is possible  to  select  the
  screenmode to use for showing the picture.
@EndNode

@Node Modifica "To Modify the Size"

 Modify Size Window:
 ===================

    It allows easy setting of the size of the printing. Here there are
  the gadgets:


  Border:
  =======

    Top & Left:
    ===========

        They allow modification of the left or top border by inserting
      a value in centimetres or printer-dots.


  Picture:
  ========

    Width & Height:
    ===============

        They allow modification of the dimensions of  the  picture  on
      the page by inserting a value in centimetres or in printer-dots.


    Keep Aspect:
    ============

        If this gadget  is  selected  by  inserting  one  of  the  two
      dimensions  of  the  picture,  the  other  one   will   be   set
      automatically to preserve the right dimensions of the image.

  Paper:
  ======

    Height:
    =======

        They allow selection of the height of the paper used.

      Note: You cannot modify the width of the paper because it depend
      ===== from the OS Printer's Preferences and the printer model.


  Page:
  =====

    You can specify a rectangle for limit the printable  area  setting
  the position relative to the top-left corner of the  paper  and  the 
  sizes. 


  Accept:
  =======

    It will accept the selected dimensions.


  Cancel:
  =======

    It will leave the  dimensions of  the  page and  the  picture
   unchanged.


    EasyPrint can print POSTERS, too.

    It is sufficient to insert, as dimensions of the  image  to  print,
  some values which exceed the page limits; so EasyPrint will mark  on
  the screen the number of pages effectively used during printing.
@EndNode

@Node Densita "Density"

  Density:
  ========

    This slider is used to  select  the  wanted  density  of  printing
  (expressed in dots per inch).

    The number of dots per inch (DPI) depends only on the printer used.
@EndNode

@Node ColoreCMG "Colour"

  Colour:
  =======

    It allows selection of which  component  of  the  colour  will  be
  printed.

  
  Color Separation:
  =================

    The act of converting an RGB color image into  CMYK  color  image.
  The act of color separation is a  technical  function  during  which
  critical  press-specific  settings such as  GCR, black ink limit and
  total ink limit are applied to the image. If  an  image  is  already
  CMYK  it  would  be  described  as being already color separated and
  would not need to be separated again.


  UCR (Under Color Removal):
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
 
    A color separation setting used on color photographs  where  cyan,
  magenta and yellow inks are removed from  dark,  neutral  areas  and
  black  ink  is swapped in instead. The advantages are a reduction in
  overall ink usage.
    
  
  GCR (Grey Component Replacement):
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
  
    A color separation setting used on color photographs  where  cyan,
  magenta and yellow inks are swapped out of an image  (in  a  balance
  that  would yield a grey value) and black ink is swapped in instead.
  The advantages  are  a  reduction  in  overall  ink  usage,  a  more
  consistent press run, and some increase in image detail.


  Ink Compensation:
  =================

    @{"OPTION NOT ENABLED!" link Registrarsi}

    Printer's inks are not completely  pure  materials.  For  example,
  there is some amount of yellow mixed  into  the  magenta  ink.  And,
  there  is  some  amount of magenta which unavoidably is found in the
  cyan ink.  The  ink  compensation  values  will  correct  for  these
  impurities.

  Magenta:  You define the amount  of  magenta  in  the  cyan  ink  in
  -=-=-=-=  percent.

  Yellow:   You define the amount of yellow  in  the  magenta  ink  in
  -=-=-=-   percent.

  In general, set the ink compensation value of:
  
  Magenta=31% 
  Yellow=40%

  for best results with Inkum Inks.

  NOTE: The ink compensation function can be  completely  disabled  by
  ===== defining 0%. You will notice that without the ink compensation
  function, a blue sky will print as purple. With the ink compensation
  function set at 31%, blue skies are blue again.


  Save:
  =====

    EasyPrint save the four planes Cyan, Magenta, Yellow and Black  on
  disk. The files will have these extensions:

    Cyan    ->  .cyn
    Magenta ->  .mag
    Yellow  ->  .yel
    Black   ->  .blk

  NOTE:   The ink compensation isn't applied on files.


  Show:
  =====

    Show on screen the four planes. To change window position you  can
  press the right-mouse button when the Cyan Window is active.

  NOTE:   The ink compensation isn't applied on windows
@EndNode

@Node Retino "Dither"

 Dither:
 =======

    This cyclic gadget allows the  selection  of what type of ditherng
   will  be  used  in the printing phase.
    
    The dithers are loaded from a directory called "Dithers",  located
   in the same directory as Easy Print.

    The dithers given are the following:

  - Floyd-Steinberg & Burkes:
    ========================

        Floyd-Steinberg is of algorytmic type, so  not  present  as  a 
      file. It is excellent for colour rendering, but needs a  printer
      really  able to  reach the specified density of printing.
      
      Burkes is similar to Floyd  but diffuses the error  on a greater 
      number of pixels, so the quality is better, but  it's  a  little 
      bit slower.

  - Halftone:
    =========

        Dither used in  typographical printing. Very  good  quality
      on printers with very high density  printing.

  - Ordered:
    ========

        Excellent quality with every printer.

  - Ordered+:
    =========

        Equal to the 'Ordered' but more defined.

  - Rhomboid:
    =========

        A variation of the Halftones.

 
 Important:
 ==========

    The unpleasant effect that can lower the quality of  the excellent  
  "Floyd-Steinberg" dithering,with inkjet printers is due  essentially  
  to two factors:

  - The printer does not reach the number of dot/inch declared on  the
    manual.

  - The paper used is of low quality. In that case it will absorb more
    ink than is necessary; so causing the blending of colours.

  To obtain further dithers it is sufficient @{"TO REGISTER" link Registrarsi}.
@EndNode

@Node Stampa "Print"

 Print:
 ======

    By pressing it the printing phase will start.

    To stop the printing you can press the close gadget  of  the
  window indicating the status (of completeness) of the printing.
@EndNode

@Node Colori "Appendix about Colours"

 Appendix about Colours:
 =======================

    On the computer screen the colours are added to the black  of  the
  monitor using the fundamental ones Red,  Green,  Blue.  Unlike  what
  happens  on  the  sheet  where  the colours are subtracted  from the
  white of the paper using their complementary ones Cyan, Magenta  and
  Yellow.

    So adding to an image any of the RGB colours means to brighten it,
  and subctracting any of these three ones means to darken it.

    On the contrary if any of the CMY colours are added  to  an  image
  they will darken  the  picture (in fact, when  blended  they produce
  black), if are subtracted they will brighten it (because they  leave
  more space to the white of the paper). 
@EndNode

@Node Stampare "How to Print in Few Minutes"

 How to Print in Few Minutes:
 ============================

    To print with EasyPrint is very simple and needs only a VERY short
  time!

    After starting EasyPrint, the steps to do are the following:

  1) To Open the window @{"PREFERENCES" link Preferenze} for setting:

    - If the picture should be smoothed in the printing phase
    - How many lines have to be elaborated for each strip

  2) To @{"LOAD" link Carica} a picture

  3) Optionally to modify the @{"BALANCING" link Bilancia} and/or to @{"CROP" link Taglia} the
     image

  4) To set the @{"DENSITY" link Densita} of printing

  5) To set the image @{"DIMENSIONS" link Modifica} on the paper

  6) To choose the @{"DITHER" link Retino} to be used for printing

  7) To press the @{"PRINT" link Stampa} gadget.

    And the print phase will start!
@EndNode

@Node StampareBW "How to Print in Black & White"

 How to Print in Black & White
 =============================

    For printing a coloured image in the black & white mode it  is
  enough to convert it with the external module "Color2Grey".
@EndNode

