@Node Moduli "How to Use External Modules"

  How to Use External Modules:
  ============================

    @{"OPTION NOT ENABLED!" link Registrarsi}
    
    Clicking on the gadget "Modules" appear a File  Requester  through
  which you can select  a  module  to  execute,  among  the  following
  modules:

    - Antique

    - Convolve

    - Negative

    - ReliefMap

    - FlipX/FlipY

    - Grey to Color

    - Color to Grey
    
    - Rotate90


    A little description:

    Antique:
    ========

      It will transform the picture into its "antique".


    Convolve:
    =========
    
      Apply a convolution matrix on the  image. It's possible to enter
    matrixs 3*3 or 5*5. Through the  gadget  "Load"  you  can  load  a
    defined  matrix  (among  20+!), besides, clicking the gadget "Save"
    you can save your matrixs.


    Negative:
    =========

      It will transform the picture into its negative.


    ReliefMap:
    ==========

      It will transform the picture into a bas-relief!


    FlipX/FlipY:
    ============

      It will flip the picture on its X axis (or Y axis).


    Color to Grey:
    ==============

      It convert a coloured picture into a  black&white  picture.  You
    can set a weight to each component RGB.
    

    Grey to Color:
    ==============

      It convert a black&white picture into a coloured picture.

    
    Rotate90:
    =========

      It rotate the picture of  90  degrees  (clockwise).  Useful  for
    vertical printings.
      
     
    UNDO Funcion:
    =============
    
      By pressing the right mouse button on the gadget "Modules" it is
    possible to restore the picture like was before to have applyed  a
    module.
@EndNode

@Node Storia "History of EasyPrint"

  Easy Print - History
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=


    v2.28:  - Added a 64 colors screen mode (AGA is sloooow in 256 cols! :(( )

            - Enhanced quality on screen in b&w mode

            - More flexible box when "Modify dimensions" (finally! :)

            - I used fonts XEN (beautiful!)

            - Fixed some (very) little bug


    v2.27:  - Fixed a stupid mungwall-hit when printing in b&w
            
            - Added a progress bar for the external modules

            - Added the module: Solarize


    v2.26:  - More flexible box in the Crop Window

            - Now the smoothing is even vertical, non only horizontal

            - New external module: Rotate90, for vertical printings.

            - Added UNDO function to external modules

            - Never again exclusive access to printer.device!


    v2.25:  - Dither Floyd-Steinberg on Deluxe Mode (256 cols)

            - Color Separation (UCR/GCR)

            - Inks Compensation (Magenta and Yellow)

            - Distinction Apply/Use in Crop window

            - Loading with external modules (reduce code size)

            - Optimized Virtual Memory

            - Optimized Crop / Backdrop box

            - Now you can reset all the balancing with a gadget

            - File-Requester keeps the name of the last loaded file 

            - You can change the unit of the device

            - Distinction Page/Paper
    

    v2.24:  - EasyPrint can use  the  British Metric System  (inches)
              besides the Decimal Metric System (centimetres).


    v2.23:  - Enabled support for external modules.
            
            - Added these special-fx as modules:

              - Antique

              - Convolve

              - Negative

              - ReliefMap

              - FlipX/FlipY

              - Grey to Color

              - Color to Grey


    v2.22:  - Fixed a bug  that  caused  enforcer  hits  when  running
              EasyPrint from CLI.

            - EasyPrint now uses the standard OS2.x commandline template.

            - Tooltype support.


Pre v2.22:  - I have no wish to write it ... it's too long!! ;)
@EndNode

@Node Verticale "How To Print in Vertical"

    How To Print in Vertical:
    =========================

      You can use the external @{"MODULE" link Moduli} called "Rotate90".
@EndNode
